clinical_study.brief_title: MK-0941 Multiple Dose Study in Japanese Patients With Type 2 Diabetes (MK-0941-011).
clinical_study.official_title: A Multiple Dose Study to Assess the Safety, Tolerability, Pharmacokinetics and Pharmacodynamics of MK-0941 in Japanese Patients With Type 2 Diabetes

brief_summary.textblock: The multiple dose study to assess the safety, tolerability, pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics of MK-0941 in Japanese patients with Type 2 Diabetes.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants Who Experienced at Least One Adverse Event (AE)
primary_outcome.time_frame: Up to 14 days after last dose of study drug
primary_outcome.description: An AE is defined as any unfavorable and unintended change in the structure, function, or chemistry of the body temporally associated with the use of the study drug, whether or not considered related to the use of the product. Participants were monitored for occurrence AEs for up to 8 days after last dose of study drug during Period 1 and for up to 14 days after last dose of study drug during Period 2.

arm_group.description: Participants received Placebo during Period 1 and MK-0941 20 mg during Period 2. There was a washout period of at least 8 days between the two treatment periods.
Participants received MK-0941 5 mg during Period 1 and Placebo during Period 2. There was a washout period of at least 8 days between the two treatment periods.
Participants received MK-0941 5 mg during Period 1 and MK-0941 20 mg during Period 2. There was a washout period of at least 8 days between the two treatment periods.
Participants received Placebo during Period 1 and MK-0941 40 mg during Period 2. There was a washout period of at least 8 days between the two treatment periods.
Participants received MK-0941 10 mg during Period 1 and Placebo during Period 2. There was a washout period of at least 8 days between the two treatment periods.
Participants received MK-0941 10 mg during Period 1 and MK-0941 40 mg during Period 2. There was a washout period of at least 8 days between the two treatment periods.

intervention.description: Placebo tablets before every meal (q.a.c) Treatment period is 5 days.
MK-0941 5 mg tablets q.a.c.; 10 mg tablets q.a.c.; 20 mg tablets q.a.c.; or 40 mg tablets q.a.c. Treatment period is 5 days.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Japanese Male or Female between 20 to 65 years of age
- Diagnosis of Type 2 Diabetes
- Patient being treated by diet and exercise alone
Exclusion Criteria:
- Patient has a history of Type 1 Diabetes
- Patient is being treated with glaucoma medications
- Patient has donated blood or participated in another clinical study in the past 12 weeks
- Patient is a regular user of any illicit drugs or has a history of drug, including alcohol, abuse
